Here are 15 objective question-answer pairs based on the document page:

1. Q: What is the purpose of a Personalausweis (identity card)?
A: An identity card is used to verify one's identity and prove their nationality.

2. Q: How can I apply for a new identity card?
A: You can apply for a new identity card online or in person at the Hamburg Service.

3. Q: What documents do I need to bring with me when applying for an identity card?
A: You will need to provide proof of identity, such as a passport, ID card, or birth certificate, and a valid photo (if not using the Speed Capture Terminal).

4. Q: How much does it cost to use the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: The terminal costs 6 EUR.

5. Q: Are there any specific requirements for taking a photo at the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: No, but please note that the terminal is not suitable for Passfotos of Säuglingen (infants) and Kleinkindern (young children).

6. Q: How long are biometric data stored after being taken with the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: Biometric data are deleted within 60 minutes or 12 hours, respectively.

7. Q: Can I use the Speed Capture Terminal for multiple documents, such as an identity card and passport?
A: Yes, the same biometric data can be used for multiple documents.

8. Q: Who is responsible for handling my personal data taken with the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: Your biometric data will only be accessed by a Sachbearbeiter (case worker) for the purpose of processing your identity card application.

9. Q: What are the opening hours of the Hamburg Service?
A: The Hamburg Service is open on Wednesdays and Thursdays from 8 am to 2:30 pm and 11:30 am to 6 pm, respectively. An appointment is required for a visit.

10. Q: Can I book an appointment online or by phone?
A: Yes, you can book an appointment online (https://www.hamburg.de/go/17584) or by calling the Hamburg Service.

11. Q: What are the general requirements for applying for an identity card?
A: You will need to provide proof of identity and a valid photo (if not using the Speed Capture Terminal).

12. Q: Can I apply for a temporary identity card if mine has been lost or stolen?
A: Yes, you can apply for a vorläufiger Personalausweis (provisional identity card) in case your original ID is lost or stolen.

13. Q: What are the specific requirements for applying for a provisional identity card?
A: You will need to provide proof of identity and a valid photo (if not using the Speed Capture Terminal), as well as evidence of loss or theft.

14. Q: Can I apply for an identity card online?
A: No, you can only apply in person at the Hamburg Service or by phone.

15. Q: Are there any additional fees associated with applying for an identity card?
A: Yes, there may be additional costs, such as the 6 EUR fee for using the Speed Capture Terminal.